OL,3,CMother withdraws son from school
OL,4,Ctransport over fears for his safety
OL,6,FEarlier this year, a number of parents
OL,7,Fprotested outside Cornwall Council's
OL,8,Foffices in Truro, with many claiming
OL,9,Ftheir children were unable to access
OL,10,Feducation because their needs were not
OL,11,Fbeing met by the council.
OL,13,FHowever, a Cornwall Council meeting in
OL,14,FMarch this year found that the number
OL,15,Fof complaints about its SEND services
OL,16,Fhad drastically reduced within the
OL,17,Flast year.
OL,19,FCouncillors were told that
OL,20,Fimprovements had been made which had
OL,21,Freduced the backlog of complaints.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G8/8
